#Explanation



- Sum of Natural Numbers using Recursion


Explanation:

The positive numbers 1, 2, 3... are known as natural numbers. The program below takes a positive integer from the user and calculates the sum up to the given number.



Example

n = 5

Output -
15


#Explanation END


package vaibhav;

public class Recursive_Natural_No {
	
	public static void natural(int i, int n, int sum) {
		
		if(n == i) {
			sum += i;
			System.out.println(sum);
			return;
		}
		
		 sum += i;
		
		natural(i+1, n , sum);
	}

	public static void main(String[] args) {
		// TODO Auto-generated method stub
//		int n = 5;
		natural(1,5,0);
	}

}
